GIVENS v. WEST VIRGINIA. No. 22,

Misc.

Decided November 24, 1958. Appellant pro se. W. W. Barron, Attorney General of West Virginia, and Fred H. Capian and George H. Mitchell, Assistant Attorneys General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The appeal is dismissed. Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari, certiorari is denied.
